				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The delay arrow hit with walled mobs is something that I have encountered on numerous occasions in Nurga. The reason I feel this is not a graphical bug or a lag issue is simple: Headshot.
<br />

<br />
I can repeatedly shoot a rooted walled mob for 2 minutes. We are talking a lot of arrows with max haste from a chanter bot and a 28 Del bow and a FQ. 
<br />
The mob does not show any damage taken nor does it give the jerking action of being hit.
<br />
As soon as root breaks and the mob moves a step, KABOOM, Fatal bow shot. If this was a lag issue/graphics bug,  I should see a whack load of spam ending in a Fatal Bowshot. Sometimes I see a lot, but more often than not I only see a few shots logged and a KABOOM. There are certain mobs between the Thabis and Joepla PH's where I can guarantee this to happen. My theory is that the arrows are indeed queueing, pending a geometry environment which allows them to have their proper effect.<br />_________________<br />Alfhild Balebane
<br />
62 Warder 
<br />
(232 AAs and climbing! THANK-YOU HEADSHOT!!)
<br />
Amazon Sisters
<br />
Bertox</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
